<div class="qna-content">
<p data-block-key="eohdz"><a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/stock-market/types-of-stocks/growth-stocks/value-vs-growth-stocks/">Value investing and growth investing</a> are two different investing styles. Usually, value stocks present an opportunity to buy shares below their actual value, and growth stocks exhibit above-average revenue and earnings growth potential.</p>
